@jmchen-g @nealwu for model zoo. Model zoos tend to be applied examples, for instance image recognition network training on a corpus such as MNIST, rather than a network building block, like an RNN cell.

RBMs can be implemented in contrib. Effectively we have DBNs if you care to stack layers.

@jmchen-g @nealwu for model zoo. Model zoos tend to be applied examples, for instance image recognition network training on a corpus such as MNIST, rather than a network building block, like an RNN cell.

RBMs can be implemented in contrib. Effectively we have DBNs if you care to stack layers.
